author: Corey Pellatt
title: Memphis Depay Has Sold More Shirts Than Anyone Else in the Premier League This Season
text:
It's not been a dream start to life at Old Trafford for Memphis Depay but he's finally got some good news.
The Dutch winger was one of the most highly-anticipated Premier League arrivals of the summer when he joined Manchester United for a reported figure of Â£30 million but he's struggled to adapt to life in England so far, scoring just once in eight league games.
The pre-season hype was obviously enough to tempt United fans to part with their cash though, as more 'Depay 7' shirts have been sold so far this season than those for any other Premier League player, according to stats released by Kitbag .
Lionel Messi sells the most shirts worldwide.
There's no big surprise behind the biggest shirt mover in world football, with Barca's Lionel Messi leading the way. Cristiano Ronaldo lands at number two behind Messi, which is something he's pretty used to by now.
Depay sits pretty at number three and his Manchester United team mate, Bastian Schweinsteiger, is fourth.
[via ESPN ]
